    Helper function for calling orcid API

    orcid_api_call.Rd

    The ORCID REST API does not require any authentication for basic querying. The OpenAPI documentation is available.

    Usage

    orcid_api_call(orcid, path = "/works")

    Arguments

    orcid

    character(1) the required orcid

    works

    character(1) the rest of the API path after the orcid part.

    Value

    an R list representation of the REST API json response

    Details

    The API typically works with the ORCID as the base resource. Therefore, an ORCID is required for this function. The path follows the documentation.

    Examples

    orcid='0000-0001-7443-925X'

orcid_api_call(orcid)
